rg/facilities/camp-silver-fir/ Active]\n |\n|-\n | [[Camp Stephens]] ||[[Alameda Council]]||[[Pinecrest Lake]] || Closed || \n|-\n | [[Camp Tahquitz]] ||[[Long Beach Area Council]]||[[Angelus Oaks, California|Angelus Oaks]] ||[https://www.longbeachbsa.org/aboutus/tahquitz/ Active]|| \n|-\n | [[Camp Tamarancho]]|| Marin Council || Farifax ||[http://www.boyscouts-marin.org/camping-and-facilities/camp-tamarancho/4057 Active]\n|\n |-\n | [[Camp Three Falls]] || Ventura County Council || Frazier Park ||[https://www.vccbsa.org/Camping/Camp%20Three%20Falls/ Active]\n|\n|-\n|Camp Verdugo Oaks\n|Verdugo Hills Council\n|\n|[https://vhcbsa.org/facilities/camp-verdugo-oaks/ Active]\n|\n|-\n | [[Camp Whitsett]] ||[[Western Los Angeles County Council]]||  ||[http://www.campwhitsett.org/ Active]|| Located in the Sequoia National Forest.\n |-\n | [[Camp Winton]] ||[[Golden Empire Council]]||[[Bear River Reservoir]] || [http://www.gec-bsa.org/camping/campwinton Active] ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Wolfeboro]] ||[[Mt Diablo Silverado Council]]||  ||[https://campwolfeboro.mdscbsa.org/ Active]|| located in Sierra Nevada Mountains near Angels Camp and Bear Valley. Started operating as a Boy Scout camp in 1928.\n |-\n | [[Camp Wolverton]] ||[[Western Los Angeles County Council]]||  || Closed || Located in the Sequoia National Park.\nClosed in 2012\n |-\n | [[Chesebrough Scout Reservation]] ||[[Silicon Valley Monterey Bay Council]]||  ||[http://svmbc.org/svmbc/campproperties/chesebrough-scout-reservation/ Active]|| Also called Camp Chesebrough, this is a 544-acre (2.2&nbsp;km\u00b2) Boy Scouts of America camp in the Santa Cruz Mountains of Santa Cruz and San Mateo counties, California.\n |-\n | [[Circle B Scout Ranch]] ||[[Old Baldy Area Council]]||  || Closed || Open from the late 1950s until 1974, it was located in the southern Sierra Nevada northeast of Lake Isabella and due west of China Lake Naval Weapons Station.\n |-\n | [[Camp Circle X|Circle X]] ||[[Los Angeles Area Council]]||[[Cedar Glen, California|Cedar Glen]]|| Active ||Camp Circle X at Big Horn.  Part of Hubert Eaton Scout Reservation.\n |-\n | [[Cutter Scout Reservation]] ||[[Pacific Skyline Council]]||[[Boulder Creek, California|Boulder Creek]] || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Firestone Scout Reservation]] ||[[Los Angeles Area Council]]||[[Brea, California|Brea]]  ||[https://www.glaacbsa.org/firestone Active]|| Located just east of State Route 57 in Tonner Canyon between Diamond Bar and Brea, California.\n |-\n | [[Forest Lawn Scout Reservation]]\naka Hubert Eaton Scout Reservation\n|[[Los Angeles Area Council]]||[[Lake Arrowhead, California|Lake Arrowhead]] ||[https://www.glaacbsa.org/Hubert_Eaton Active]|| Located 3 miles (5&nbsp;km) east of Lake Arrowhead, California, formerly known as the Lake Arrowhead Scout Camps. The Forest Lawn Scout Reservation consists of five active and one closed Boy and Cub Scout resident camps on more than 2,000 acres in the San Bernardino National Forest.  The six camps are:\n{|\n|-\n|\n* Circle X Ranch at Big Horn\n* Camp Pepperdine,\n* Camp Pitchess, formerly Camp Cedar (closed)\n|\n* Camp Pollock \u2013 adjacent to what was once Camp Pitchess\n* John Wayne Outpost \u2013 wilderness camping area\n* Northrop Family Camp\n|}\n |-\n | [[Glacial Trails Scout Ranch]] ||[[Golden Empire Council]]||[[Cisco Grove, California|Tahoe National Forest]] || Closed || Reopened as Camp Robert L. Cole.\n  |-\n | [[Holcomb Valley Scout Ranch]] ||[[San Gabriel Valley Council]]|| Big Bear ||[https://www.glaacbsa.org/holcomb Active]|| Located north of Big Bear Lake in the old mining district of Belleville in the Holcomb Valley, on the site of the old Hitchcock Ranch.\n |-\n | [[Holt Scout Ranch]] ||[[San Gabriel Valley Council]]||  || [http://www.lafavre.us/holt/Holt_Scout_Ranch.htm Closed] || Closed in 1974. Previously known as Camp Cedar Canyon\n |-\n | [[Irvine Ranch Outdoor Education Center]] ||[[Orange County Council]]||[[Orange, California|Orange]] ||[https://www.outdooreducationcenter.org/ Active]|| 190 Acres\n |-\n | [[Jubilee Scout Ranch]] ||[[Western Los Angeles County Council]]||  || Closed || Closed in 2003.\n |-\n | [[Log Cabin Wilderness Camp]] ||[[Los Angeles Area Council]]||[[Tioga Pass Road]] ||[https://www.glaacbsa.org/log_cabin Closed]|| Closed in 2016. \n |-\n | [[Long Beach Sea Base]] ||[[Long Beach Area Council]]||[[Long Beach, California|Long Beach]] ||[https://www.longbeachbsa.org/aboutus/seabase/ Active]||\n |-\n | [[Lost Valley Scout Reservation]] ||[[Orange County Council]]||[[Warner Springs, California|Warner Springs]]||[https://www.ssrlv.org/ Active]|| Schoepe Scout Reservation at Lost Valley\n |-\n | [[Marina Wilderness Camp]] ||  ||  ||  ||\n |-\n | [[Mataguay Scout Reservation]] ||[[San Diego-Imperial Council]]\n|[[Santa Ysabel, California|Santa Ysabel]]\n|[https://camping.sdicbsa.org/MSR/ Active]\n|\n |-\n | [[Newport Sea Base]] ||[[Orange County Council]]||[[Newport Beach, California|Newport Beach]]||[https://www.newportseabase.org/ Active]||\n |-\n | [[Oso Lake]] ||[[Orange County Council]]||[[Rancho Santa Margarita, California|Rancho Santa Margarita]] ||[https://www.osolake.org/ Active]|| \n |-\n | [[Pardee Scout Sea Base]] ||[[Western Los Angeles County Council]]||[[Marina Del Rey, California|Marina Del Rey]] || Closed ||Closed in 2008\n|-\n | [[Pendola Sierra Adventure base]] ||[[Greater Yosemite Council]]||[[Emigrant Wilderness Area]] || [http://www.yosemitescouting.org/camping/pendola-sierra-adventure-base/51881 Active] ||\n|-\n | [[Rancho Alegre (California)|Rancho Alegre]] ||[[Los Padres Council]]||[[Lake Cachuma]] ||[https://www.lpcbsa.org/camping/ Active]||\n|-\n | [[Rancho Las Flores]] ||[[Orange County Council]]||  || Closed || At [[Camp Pendelton]]\n |-\n | [[Rancho Los Mochos]] ||[[Oakland Area Council (California)|Oakland Area Council]] / [[San Francisco Bay Area Council]]||[[Livermore, California|Livermore]]||[http://www.sfbac-history.org/RLM.html Active]  ||1945\u2013present.  Located in the hills south of Livermore.  640 acres. Three camping areas: Blue Oak Ridge, Manzanita Flats, and Deadwood.\n |-\n | [[Sierra North High Aadventure|Sierra North High Adventure]] ||  ||  ||  ||\n |-\n | [[Stockton Sea Scout Base]] ||  ||  ||  ||\n |-\n | [[Three Falls Camp]] ||[[Ventura County Council]]||  ||[https://www.vccbsa.org/camping/camp-three-falls/ Active]\n|\n |-\n | [[Trask Scout Reservation]] ||[[San Gabriel Valley Council]]||[[Monrovia, California|Monrovia]] ||[https://www.glaacbsa.org/trask Active]|| Located above the Sawpit Dam off of Monrovia Canyon Park.\n |-\n | [[Verdugo Pines]] ||  ||[[Valyermo, California|Valyermo]]\n| Closed ||Sold in 1963\n |-\n | [[Wente Scout Reservation / Willits Scout Reservation]] ||Oakland Area Council /  [[San Francisco Bay Area Council]]||[[Willits, California|Willits]]||[http://www.sfbac.org/camping/wentescoutreservation Active] ||1959\u2013present. 2200 acres located in the hills east of Willits.  First camping took place in October 1959, and the first summer camp took place in July 1964. It was renamed to Wente Scout Reservation in 1978 in honor of San Francisco Council Board Member and Bank of America President Carl F. Wente.\n |-\n | [[Will J. Reid Reservation]] ||[[Long Beach Area Council]]||[[Long Beach, California|Long Beach]]|| Closed ||Closed in 2010\n|}\n\n=== Colorado ===\n{{Details|Scouting in Colorado}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n |-\n | [[Ben Delatour Scout Ranch]] || Longs Peak Council ||[[Red Feather Lakes, Colorado]] || Active || Encompassing 3,200 acres at Red Feather Lakes, Colorado, it includes four Scout camps. \n{|\n|-\n|\n* Jack Nicol Cub Scout Camp\n* Camp Charles Jeffrey\n|\n* Camp Ruth Coffin\n* Elkhorn High Adventure Base\n|}\n |-\n |