ivalleybsa.org/camping/campeastman Active] || Located near Nauvoo, IL.\n |-\n | [[Camp Heffernan]] || Corn Belt Council || Normal, IL || Sold || Now known as the Timber Pointe Outdoor Center.\n |-\n | [[Camp Illinek]] || Abraham Lincoln Council || Chatham, IL || [https://web.archive.org/web/20151029030934/http://www.alincolnbsa.org/camp/illinek/camp_illinek.htm Active] ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Joy]] || Greater St. Louis Area Council || Carlyle, IL || [https://stlbsa.org/activities/camping/camp-properties/camp-joy-2/ Active] || \n |-\n | [[Camp Ki Shau Wau]] || W.D. Boyce Council || Carlyle, IL || Sold || Sold in 1989. \n |-\n | [[Camp Lakota (Illinois)|Camp Lakota]] || Pathway to Adventure Council || Woodstock, IL || [http://pathwaytoadventure.org/camping/allseason Active] || \n |-\n | [[Camp Lowden]] || Blackhawk Area Council || Oregon, IL || [http://www.camplowden.org/ Active] ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Mansur]] || Moline Area Council || Between Carbon Cliff, IL and Silvis, IL || Sold ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Napowan]] || Northwest Suburban Area Council || Wild Rose, WI || [http://www.napowan.org/ Active] ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Na-Se-Us-Kuk]] || Fort Armstrong Area Council || Illinois City, IL || Active || Camp changed name to Loud Thunder, currently used by Illowa Council. \n |-\n | [[Camp Pearl]] ||  || Tennessee, IL ||  || <!-- see patch, \"Camp Pearl\", \"Prairie Council BSA\" Troop 315 ref camping in 2011 -->\n |-\n | [[Camp Robert Drake]] || Prairielands Council || Fairmount, IL || [http://www.campdrake.com/ Active] ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Robert Faries]] ||  || Decatur, IL ||  || Lincoln Trails, can find patches with 1979 paper<ref>{{cite web|url=http://herald-review.com/camp-robert-faries/image_24951216-2d08-11e2-b2c4-0019bb2963f4.html|title=Camp Robert Faries|publisher=}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Sauk Trails]] || Great Sauk Trail Council || Frankfort, IL || Active ||  Camp Manitoqua is off of Sauk Trail Road.\n |-\n | [[Camp Saukenauk]] || Mississippi Valley Council || Mendon || [http:/