ly 2019}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Paxson Boy Scout Camp|Camp Paxson]] || Western Montana Council || Seeley Lake, MT || Active || Situated in [[Lolo National Forest]].\n |-\n | [[K-M Scout Ranch]] || Montana Council || Hilger, MT || Active || Renovated in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.greatfallstribune.com/story/news/2019/03/25/renovations-k-m-scout-ranch-ready-camp-summer-bsa-lewistown/3267985002/|last=Inbody|first=Kristen|date=25 March 2019|title=Renovations to K-M Scout Ranch ready camp for summer|website=Great Falls Tribune|accessdate=21 July 2019}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Grizzly Base Camp]] || Montana Council || Columbia Falls, MT || Active ||\n|}\n\n=== Nebraska ===\n{{Details|Scouting in Nebraska}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n |-\n | [[Camp Augustine]] || Overland Trails Council  || Near Doniphan, NE  || Active || 1945\u2013Present. Camp Augustine is a 160-acre camp along the banks of the Platte River between Grand Island and Doniphan, Nebraska<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://overlandtrailscouncil.com/camping/|title=Camping|website=Overland Trails Council}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Butterfield]] || Mid-America Council  || Near Orchard, NE || Closed || Camp Butterfield was located 13 miles north of Orchard, Nebraska and composed 160 acres of rolling sandhills<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mac-bsa.org:80/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=95&Itemid=80|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071121231928/http://mac-bsa.org:80/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=95&Itemid=80|url-status=dead|archive-date=November 21, 2007|title=Mid-America Council, BSA \u2013 Camp Butterfield|date=November 21, 2007}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Cedars]] || Mid-America Council || Near Cedar Bluffs, NE || Active || 1939\