998/gs80826-.htm|title=Garden State EnviroNet \u2013 EnviroNews|date=11 July 2002|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020711220728/http://www.gsenet.org/library/11gsn/1998/gs80826-.htm|archivedate=11 July 2002}}</ref> || [[Oakland, NJ]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.camptamarackbsa.org/|title=New Page 1|website=www.camptamarackbsa.org}}</ref> || Closed<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.users.nac.net/axtell/Tamarac.html | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080511220514/http://www.users.nac.net/axtell/Tamarac.html | url-status = dead | archive-date = 2008-05-11 | title = Tamarack}}</ref> ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Todd]] || Alexander Hamilton Council of Hudson County, NJ. || Oakland, NJ || Closed 1991 || near Ramapo Mountain State Forest\n |-\n | [[Camp Towadena]] || Alexander Hamilton Council of Hudson County, NJ. || Sandyston, NJ || || On Fairview Lake near Camp NoBeBoSco\n |-\n | [[Camp Twin Echo]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Watchung]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Winnebago]] ||Patriots' Path Council ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Yaw Paw]] || Northern New Jersey Council || Mahwah, NJ || ||\n |-\n | [[Joseph A. Citta Scout Reservation]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Kittatinny Mountain Scout Reservation]] ||Thomas A. Edison Council; Central Jersey Council ||Branchville, NJ  ||Closed as a BSA camp || Now part of Stokes State Forest, camp sites still available through NJ Division of Parks & Forestry \n |-\n | [[Mt. Allamuchy Scout Reservation]]||Patriots' Path Council ||  ||  || \n |-\n | [[Ocean County Council Reservation]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Pine Hill Scout Reservation]] || Garden State Council/Camden County  || Pine Hill, NJ || [http://www.gardenstatescouting.org/pinehill Active] || \n |-\n | [[Mortimer L. Schiff Scout Reservation]] || Boy Scouts of America || Mendham, New Jersey || Closed || This was a major Boy Scout training facility for almost 50 years.  It was closed in 1979.  It was the location of the first [[Wood Badge (Boy Scouts of America)|Wood Badge]] courses held in the United States.\n |-\n | [[Winnebago Scout Reservation]] ||Patriots' Path Council ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Wood Lake Scout Reservation]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Yards Creek Scout Reservation]] ||  ||  ||Closed || \n|}\n\n=== New Mexico ===\n{{Details|Scouting in New Mexico}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n |-\n | [[Black Range Cavalcade]] || [[Yucca Council]] || Winston, NM || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Dale Resler]] || [[Yucca Council]] || Cloudcroft, NM || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Gorham Scout Ranch]] || [[Great Southwest Council]] || Albuquerque, NM || Active || Formerly known as Camp Frank Rand. \n |-\n | [[Camp Kidd (New Mexico)|Camp Kidd]] || ||  || Closed ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Tres Ritos]] || [[South Plains Council]] || Vadito, NM || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Dowling Aquatic Base]] || [[Conquistador Council]] || Carlsbad, NM || Active || Situated on the Pecos River.\n |-\n | [[Philmont Scout Ranch]] || [[Boy Scouts of America National Council]] || Cimarron, NM ||  Active ||\n |-\n | [[Wehinahpay Mountain Camp]] || [[Conquistador Council]] || Sacramento, NM || Active ||\n|}\n\n=== New York ===\n{{Details|Scouting in New York}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n |-\n | [[Adirondack HA Base]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Alpine Scout Camp]] || [[Greater New York Councils]] || [[Alpine, NJ]] || ||\n |-\n | [[Baiting Hollow Scout Camp]] ||[[Suffolk County Council (Boy Scouts of America)|Suffolk County Council]]\n|[[Wa