on Lake\n |-\n | [[Camp Tichora]] || Four Lakes Council || Markesan, WI || Closed ||\n |-\n | [[Bay-Lakes Council#Former camps|Camp Twin Lakes]] || Bay Lakes Council || Waupaca, WI || Closed || Former Webelos resident camp\n |-\n | [[Chin-Be-Gota Scout Reservation]] || Formerly Kedeka Area Council || Birnamwood, WI  || Closed ||\n |-\n | [[Bay-Lakes Council#Gardner Dam Scout Camp|Gardner Dam Camp]] ||  Bay Lakes Council  || White Lake, WI ||  Active ||\n |-\n | [[Ed Bryant Scout Reservation]] ||  Glacier's Edge Council  ||  Mauston, WI  ||  Active || Formerly known as Camp Castle Rock; climbing tower.\n |-\n |-\n | [[Fred C. Andersen Scout Reservation]] || Northern Star Council || Houlton, WI || [https://web.archive.org/web/20130629045939/http://camping.nsbsa.org/Camps/FredCAndersen.aspx Active] || Located on the banks of the St. Croix River near Houlton, WI.\n |-\n | [[Three Harbors Council#Indian Mound Scout Reservation|Indian Mound Scout Reservation]] ||  Three Harbors Council  || Oconomowoc, WI ||  Active ||  Cub Scout camp\n |-\n | [[Bay-Lakes Council#Camps|Jax Camp]] ||  Bay Lakes Council  || Sturgeon Bay, WI  ||  Active ||  Rustic Boy Scout camp, located in Door County.\n |-\n | [[L.E. Philips Scout Reservation]] || Chippewa Valley Council  || Rice Lake, WI  || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Three Harbors Council#LeFeber Northwoods Camps|LeFeber Northwoods Camps]] || Three Harbors Council ||  Laona, WI  || Closed || Sold in 2015.\n |-\n | [[Ma-Ka-Ja-Wan Scout Reservation]] || Northeast Illinois Council || Pearson, WI || [http://www.makajawan.com/ Active]  ||  Ma-Ka-Ja-Wan consists of over 1,500 acres of beautiful forest, six spring-fed lakes, and a natural creek. The reservation is home to two full-service camps, a wilderness camp, a high adventure base, and a horse ranch.\n |-\n | [[Bay-Lakes Council#Former camps|Maywood Wilderness Scout Camps]] ||  Bay-Lakes Council  || Hancock, WI  || Inactive || Sold in 2014.\n |-\n | [[Napowan Adventure Base]] || Pathway to Adventure Council || Wild Rose, WI  || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Northern Wisconsin National Canoe Base]] || Boy Scouts of America  || Boulder Junction, WI || Closed || Closed in 1983.\n |-\n | [[Three Harbors Council#Robert S. Lyle Scout Reservation|Robert S. Lyle Scout Reservation]] || Three Harbors Council  || Elcho, WI ||  Inactive || Closed in 2015.\n |-\n | [[Samoset Council#Tesomas Scout Camp|Tesomas Scout Camp]] || Samoset Council  || Rhinelander, WI  || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Tomahawk Scout Reservation]] || Northern Star Council || Birchwood, WI || Active || 3,100 acres located near Long Lake, WI.\n|}\n\n=== Wyoming ===\n{{Details|Scouting in Wyoming}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n |-\n | [[Camp Buffalo Bill]] || Greater Wyoming Council || Cody, WY ||Active ||Located 7 miles east of [[Yellowstone National Park]] entrance.\n |-\n | [[Camp Jack]] || Longs Peak Council || Cheyenne, WY || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Laramie Peak]] || Longs Peak Council || Wheatland, WY || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Loll]] || Trapper Trails Council || Ashton, WY || Active || Situated on Lake of the Woods near [[Yellowstone National Park]].\n |-\n | [[Camp New Fork]] || Trapper Trails Council || Cora, WY || Active || Situated on the lower New Fork Lake.\n |-\n | [[Chimney Park Scout Camp]] || Longs Peak Council || Laramie, WY || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Teton HA Base]] || Great Salt Lake Council || Jackson, WY  || Active ||\n |}\n\n== Outside the 50 US states ==\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=